<cite id="part_1">[[#part 1 back|Note (1):]]</cite> Since version 8.1 PostgreSQL provides partitioning support through check constraints.<ref>{{Citation
  | publisher = PostgreSQL community
  | url       = https://www.postgresql.org/docs/8.1/static/release-8-1.html
  | series    = Developer
  | title     = Documents
  | chapter   = Release
  | number    = 8.1
  }}</ref>

<cite id="raima_2">[[#raima 2 back|Note (2):]]</cite> Raima Database Manager 14.0 requires the application programs to select the correct partition (using range, hash or composite techniques) when adding data, but the ''database union'' functionality allows all partitions to be read as a single database.<ref>{{Citation
  | publisher = Raima
  | url       = http://docs.raima.com/rdm/14_0/#Glossary/dbname_spec.htm
  | title     = User's Guide
  | chapter   = Database Unions
  | number    = 14.0
  }}</ref>

